f=Engineering/rank/custom/structured-data-geo/SKILL.md · in=structured-data-geo rank's execution two connected things: **structured data** (Schema.org markup tells search engines what page's content *means*) **GEO/AEO** (Generative Engine Answer Engine Optimization citable answer engines like Google Overviews, ChatGPT, Perplexity). about machine-understanding content, increasingly visibility won lost search shifts links answers. · p=Search bifurcating: classic blue links plus AI-generated answers cite sources. Structured data always helped search engines understand pages; helps engines decide what cite. page that's technically perfect semantically opaque gets neither rich results citations. rank makes content machine-understandable execution layer under kai's strategy about what content exist. · wu=Triggers: "schema markup," "structured data," "rich results," "GEO," "AI Overviews," "get cited ChatGPT/Perplexity," "AEO," "llms.txt," any machine-understanding-of-content task. · st:/ Protocol=`A structured-data / GEO task \· -> SCHEMA: the right Schema.org types for the content (Article, Product, Organization, LocalBusiness…) \· validated \· rendered in output (technical-seo-execution's rendering seam) \· RESPECT current deprecations: HowTo deprecated (Sept 2023); FAQ rich results gov/health only (Aug 2023) \· -> GEO/AEO: content structured for AI citation — clear answers, extractable facts, entity clarity,` · in=**Right schema types, validated, rendered.** Match Schema.org types actual content (Article, Product, Organization, BreadcrumbList, LocalBusiness…), validate against Google's structured-data requirements, ensure it's *rendered* output JS-injected schema crawler never sees useless rendering seam again). **Respect current deprecations.** SEO facts dated: HowTo schema deprecated (Sept 2023); FAQ rich results restricted government/health (Aug 2023) existing FAQPage commercial site still aid citation isn't Google rich-result win, new ones aren't recommended purpose. Core Web Vitals use INP. Treat dated (verify current guidance high-stakes decisions). **GEO machine-answerability.** AI-engine citation: clear, extractable answers near top; unambiguous entities facts; content structured lift citable statement. technical markup meets content rank owns markup, Brand Studio (lena/kai) owns substance. **AI-crawler access decision.** Whether allow crawlers (GPTBot, PerplexityBot, Google-Extended) business choice trade-off: blocked citation, allowed content used answers. Surface (llms.txt, robots directives); operator/kai decides, rank implements. **rank specs; others substance-and-implement.** rank specifies schema technical GEO requirements; mia implements markup, *content* earns citations Brand Studio's (lena's writing, kai's strategy). rank doesn't write content set strategy. **Through gate.** Schema GEO markup changes ship through normal path mia implements, dev reviews, quinn gates. Malformed schema cause manual actions, it's reviewed, sprayed. · of=`## Structured Data / GEO: [page/site] \· Schema: [types \· validated ✓ \· in rendered output ✓ \· deprecations respected (HowTo/FAQ)] \· GEO/AEO: [extractable answers \· entity clarity \· AI-crawler access decision → operator/kai] \· Boundary: [rank specs markup ✓ \· content substance → lena/kai \· implementation → mia] \· Path: [mia implement \· dev review \· quinn gate]` · pr=**Right schema, validated, rendered** markup crawler never sees useless., **Respect dated deprecations** HowTo gone, FAQ restricted, INP FID; verify high-stakes., **GEO machine-answerability** extractable answers, clear entities, citability., **AI-crawler access operator/kai decision** rank surfaces trade-off, implements choice., **rank specs markup; Brand Studio owns substance** clean boundary., **Through gate** malformed schema risks manual actions; reviewed, sprayed. · f=plugin schema/GEO method (Schema.org Google guidelines directly), labeled reduced-automation., Uncertain schema type earns rich results check current Google guidance (dated facts change); don't add speculative markup risks manual action., Content isn't citable enough GEO that's content-strategy gap lena/kai, markup fix; hand over. · b:with Other Skills=**kai (Brand Studio)**: SEO AI-search strategy measurement; **lena**: citable content itself. rank owns technical markup only., **technical-seo-execution** (sibling): rendering (schema output) crawlability GEO depends on., **claude-seo-integration** (sibling): `/seo schema` `/seo geo` deepen installed., **mia**: implements schema markup components; **aegis**: schema/structured data user input injection surface., **dev/quinn**: markup changes pass review gate.